<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FC6BD9FFFBA9FE32" box="[919,1029,460,486]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Ascomata</emphasis>
140–160 × 190–250 μm (
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FAC8D9F8FAEFFE37" box="[1332,1347,459,483]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">x</emphasis>
= 147 × 217.5 µm, n = 5), semi-immersed, uniloculate, solitary, subglobose to ovoid, dark-brown to black, ostiolate, lacking setae. 
<taxonomicName id="4C764D707E1CFF91FF2EDA27FE96FDFA" box="[210,314,532,558]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Peraceae" genus="Peridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FF2EDA27FE96FDFA" box="[210,314,532,558]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Peridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
10–20 µm wide, comprising 2–3 layers of dark-brown to pale brown cells, arranged in a 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FAA0DA26FF5FFD86" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">textura angularis</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FEFEDA0BFE29FD86" box="[258,389,568,594]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Paraphyses</emphasis>
hyaline, smooth-walled, cylindrical, with a round tip, septate, apically free, 20–45 μm long, at the basis 4–6 μm wide. 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FE68DA6FFE68FDA2" box="[404,452,604,630]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Asci</emphasis>
35–40 × 8–10 μm (
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FD55DA68FD14FDA7" box="[681,696,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">x</emphasis>
= 37.5 × 9 μm, n = 20), 6–8-spored, unitunicate, broad cylindrical to clavate, tapering to apex and base, or rounded at apex, pedicellate at base, sometimes sessile, smooth-walled. 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FF74DA97FEABFD6A" box="[136,263,676,702]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Ascospores</emphasis>
7–10 × 4–5 μm (
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FE20DA92FE47FD6F" box="[476,491,673,699]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">x</emphasis>
= 8.5 × 4.5 μm, n = 20), cylindrical, sometimes slightly curved, tapering towards rounded ends, hyaline, smooth-walled, aseptate, contents granular. 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FC79DAFBFB92FD36" bold="true" box="[901,1086,712,738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Asexual morph</emphasis>
: developed on PDA. 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FAC4DAFAFF75FCD2" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Vegetative hyphae</emphasis>
2–6.5 μm wide, hyaline, smooth-walled, septate, branched. 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FC86DADFFC1BFCD2" box="[890,951,748,774]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Setae</emphasis>
not observed. 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FBA7DADFFAACFCD2" box="[1115,1280,748,774]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Conidiophores</emphasis>
hyaline to pale brown, smooth-walled, unbranched. 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FDDCDB23FCAFFCFE" box="[544,771,784,810]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
13–15 × 3.5–5 μm (
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FC14DB3EFC5BFCF3" box="[1000,1015,781,807]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">x</emphasis>
= 14 × 4.5 μm, n = 10), hyaline to pale brown, cylindrical to clavate, monoblastic, holoblastic, integrated, terminal, cylindrical, each with single conidium. 
<taxonomicName id="4C764D707E1CFF91FF74DB6BFF4EFCA6" box="[136,226,856,882]" class="Arthoniomycetes" family="Arthoniaceae" genus="Conidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Arthoniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="148" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FF74DB6BFF4EFCA6" box="[136,226,856,882]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Conidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
9–16 × 2–5 μm (
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FE58DB66FE1FFCBB" box="[420,435,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">x</emphasis>
= 12.5 × 3.5 μm, n = 20), hyaline, aseptate, smooth-walled, cylindrical, both ends rounded, contents granular. 
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FEA2DB4FFE4AFC42" box="[350,486,892,918]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Appressoria</emphasis>
single or short chains, dark brown, irregular, but often to navicular in outline, the margin entire to undulate, 5–12 × 4–7 µm, (
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FD84DBAEFD2BFC63" box="[632,647,925,951]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">x</emphasis>
= 8.5 × 5.5 μm, n = 20).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC936F37E1CFF91FF41DBF7FAF6FBF2" blockId="5.[136,1452,459,1170]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis id="B902EAE17E1CFF91FF41DBF7FE11FC0A" box="[189,445,964,990]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Culture characteristics</emphasis>
: Colonies growing on PDA, circular, umbonate, rough and wrinkled at surface, edge entire, grey to dark in center, aerial mycelium reaching 
<quantity id="4C8E9B167E1CFF91FD5BDBDBFD59FBD7" box="[679,757,1000,1027]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="148" unit="mm" value="85.0">85 mm</quantity>
in 7 days at room temperature, pale grey to dark grey, conidia in mass orange, mycelium superficial and partially immersed, branched, septate, hyaline to dark grey, smooth.
</paragraph>
